#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Compatibility layers"
msgstr "兼容性层"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Netty trying to determine whether virtual threads are available"
msgstr "Netty 试图确定虚拟线程是否可用"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Many libraries include compatibility layers to support multiple JDK versions."
"\n"
"Typically, they rely on reflection to determine whether features like "
"virtual threads are available."
msgstr "许多库都包含兼容层，以支持多个 JDK 版本。通常，它们依靠反射来确定虚拟线程等功能是否可用。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In the Quarkus ecosystem, this is common in low-level libraries such as "
"Netty or Vert.x.\n"
"But in reality, we see this pattern everywhere."
msgstr "在 Quarkus 生态系统中，这种情况在 Netty 或 Vert.x 等低级库中很常见，但在现实中，我们随处可见这种模式。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"We should avoid this. It has a cost, and that cost is paid at **every "
"single** startup of every application using these libraries."
msgstr "我们应该避免这种情况。这样做是有代价的，使用这些库的每个应用程序在 *每次* 启动时都要付出代价。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Multi-release JARs are not perfect.\n"
"They're harder to maintain, harder to test, and not always well supported by "
"IDEs.\n"
"But they do solve this problem.\n"
"And I would argue that, as library and framework authors, it's our "
"responsibility to ensure the cost is paid once at build time, not at every "
"application startup."
msgstr ""
"多版本 JAR "
"并不完美。它们更难维护、更难测试，而且并不总是能得到集成开发环境的良好支持。但它们确实解决了这个问题。我认为，作为库和框架的作者，我们有责任确保在构建时支付一次成本，而不是在每次应用程序启动时支付。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Together with Georgios, we decided to experiment with rewriting the bytecode "
"of some of these libraries at build time to remove the reflective calls and "
"replace them with direct invocations,\n"
"when the application was targeting a Java version that supports the feature."
msgstr "与 Georgios 一起，我们决定尝试在构建时重写其中一些库的字节码，以移除反射调用，取而代之的是直接调用。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It's a bit of a hack, and definitely not something we want to maintain long "
"term, but it was a great way to validate the idea and score a few quick wins."
""
msgstr "这有点像 \"黑客\"，我们肯定不想长期坚持，但这是验证想法和取得一些快速成功的好方法。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Reading annotations"
msgstr "阅读注释"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This one isn't new to us: one of the reasons we wrote Quarkus in the first "
"place was to avoid reading annotations at runtime."
msgstr "这对我们来说并不陌生：我们当初编写 Quarkus 的原因之一就是为了避免在运行时读取注释。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"For most of our use cases, we can process annotations at build time and "
"generate the necessary bytecode so there's no need to inspect them at "
"runtime.\n"
"Jandex, our annotation indexer, is a fantastic tool for this, and we use it "
"extensively in Quarkus.\n"
"But... there are still cases where annotations are read at runtime, even in "
"Quarkus."
msgstr ""
"对于我们的大多数用例，我们可以在构建时处理注释，并生成必要的字节码，因此无需在运行时检查它们。我们的注释索引器 Jandex "
"就是这样一款出色的工具，我们在 Quarkus 中广泛使用了它。但是......即使在 Quarkus 中，仍有在运行时读取注释的情况。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Why is reading annotations so costly?\n"
"Because parsing them has a cost. It happens the first time you try to access "
"them at runtime, and the JDK then creates proxy instances to expose the "
"annotation values."
msgstr "为什么阅读注释的成本如此之高？因为解析注解是有代价的。第一次尝试在运行时访问注解时，JDK 就会创建代理实例来公开注解值。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Netty and marker annotations"
msgstr "净值和标记注释"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Netty trying to determine if a `ChannelHandler` is sharable"
msgstr "Netty 试图确定 `ChannelHandler` 是否可共享"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Netty case is particularly interesting because it reads annotations to "
"determine the capabilities of interface implementations."
msgstr "Netty 案例尤其有趣，因为它通过读取注释来确定接口实现的能力。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"For this kind of use case, we recommend using marker interfaces or methods "
"instead of annotations."
msgstr "对于这种用例，我们建议使用标记接口或方法，而不是注释。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Georgios once again resorted to bytecode rewriting to eliminate the "
"annotation lookup.\n"
"Again, this isn't something we want to maintain in the long term."
msgstr "Georgios 再次通过字节码重写来消除注释查找。同样，这也不是我们想要长期保持的。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Hibernate ORM"
msgstr "Hibernate ORM"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Hibernate ORM is also extremely interesting in this context."
msgstr "在这种情况下，Hibernate ORM 也非常有趣。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The first important point is that, with Hibernate ORM, in Quarkus, we still "
"build the metadata at runtime.\n"
"That means we end up reading a lot of annotations at runtime.\n"
"A long-term effort has already started to improve this situation,\n"
"but it's a significant undertaking and will take time before we can move "
"metadata building to build time instead."
msgstr ""
"重要的第一点是，在 Quarkus 中使用 Hibernate ORM "
"时，我们仍在运行时构建元数据。这意味着我们最终要在运行时读取大量注释。为了改善这种情况，我们已经开始了长期的努力，但这是一项艰巨的任务，我们还需要时间才能将元数据构建转移到构建时间。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Let's set that aside for now."
msgstr "我们暂且不谈这个。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"What's also interesting is that Hibernate ORM collects metadata about its "
"own annotations at runtime, both Hibernate-specific annotations and JPA "
"annotations.\n"
"And that's a lot of annotations, and a lot of metadata to process."
msgstr ""
"同样有趣的是，Hibernate ORM 会在运行时收集自身注解的元数据，包括 Hibernate 特有的注解和 JPA "
"注释。这就需要处理大量的注解和元数据。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid "Hibernate ORM collecting metadata about its own annotations"
msgstr "Hibernate ORM 收集有关自身注释的元数据"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"For example, for each JPA or Hibernate annotation, it determines the "
"annotation target (class, method, field), or whether it is inherited."
msgstr "例如，对于每个 JPA 或 Hibernate 注释，它都会确定注解的目标（类、方法、字段），或注解是否被继承。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In the end, this results in a substantial amount of annotation processing "
"for something that changes very rarely."
msgstr "最终，对于很少发生变化的内容来说，这将导致大量的注释处理工作。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I identified this issue some time ago, and our colleague Luca Molteni from "
"the Hibernate team will be looking into it soon.\n"
"We're not yet sure how easy it will be to fix, but you get the idea.\n"
"Whenever possible, this kind of metadata should be resolved once and for all."
"\n"
"And you should be able to enforce its correctness with tests to ensure it "
"remains accurate and up to date."
msgstr ""
"我发现这个问题已经有一段时间了，我们 Hibernate 团队的同事卢卡-莫尔特尼（Luca "
"Molteni）很快就会对此进行调查。我们还不确定这个问题有多容易解决，但你应该明白这一点。只要有可能，就应该一劳永逸地解决这类元数据问题。而且你应该能够通过测试来强制执行其正确性，以确保它保持准确和最新。"

#: _posts/2026-02-24-leyden-1.adoc
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Hopefully, we'll be able to improve this soon.\n"
"And the nice part is that any improvement here will benefit all applications "
"using Hibernate ORM, not just Quarkus applications."
msgstr ""
"希望我们能尽快改进这一点。最重要的是，任何改进都将惠及所有使用 Hibernate ORM 的应用程序，而不仅仅是 Quarkus 应用程序。"

